  "texts": [
    "There could also be subtler impacts on development.",
    "Children in a VR experience displayed worse impulse control than children using two-dimensional video (Bailey et al., 2019), and VR can implant false memories in children (Segovia & Bailenson, 2009), although the longterm effects of this are unknown.",
    "Children tend to perceive conversational agentseven disembodied ones like Amazon's Alexa and Apple's Siri-as \"alive\" (Lovato et al., 2019), but treat them as \"servants\" and use tones not appropriate for interpersonal communication (Bylieva et al., 2021).",
    "13 Future research should investigate whether IXR could lead to harmful, parasocial relationships and how that could affect children's ability to function in physical society or disrupt kinematic development (Miehlbradt et al., 2021).",
    "The final issue in this section is platforms' direct manipulation of users' psychological states."
  ],
